					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 22 sheep left with the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Śiṟu-Paḻuvūr for burning a lamp in the temple of Tiruvālandurai-Mahādēva (in the day time) with a <hi rend="italic">piḍi</hi> of ghee, by <hi rend="bold">Araiyaṉ Dēvaṉ of Maṇaṟkuḍi</hi> in Perumpuliyūr in Poygāi-nāḍu. Perumbuliyur is a village situated in the present Tanjavur taluk.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
